<article>
    <h1>Credit Suisse may cut up to&#xD;&#xA;500 Swiss jobs in wider re&#xAD;vamp</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200827/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-27"><time>2020-08-27</time></a>
        - <span>BUSINESS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>ZURICH • Credit Suisse Group may cut as many as 500 jobs in Switzer­land as it cuts branches and ab­sorbs a wholly owned sub­sidiary as part of a wider re­vamp un­veiled last month.</p>
    <p>Mr An­dre Helfen­stein, head of the lender’s Swiss Uni­ver­sal Bank, made the es­ti­mate on a con­fer­ence call on Tues­day af­ter the com­pany said it will in­te­grate the Neue Aar­gauer Bank unit un­der the Credit Suisse brand as part of a plan to save about 100 mil­lion francs (S$150 mil­lion) an­nu­ally start­ing in 2022.</p>
    <p>Chief ex­ec­u­tive Thomas Gottstein an­nounced his first ma­jor re­vamp of the Swiss lender at the end of last month, sim­pli­fy­ing the bank’s com­pli­cated struc­ture.</p>
    <p>The ini­tia­tive in­cludes a new cost sav­ings pro­gramme, and Credit Suisse will merge its ad­vi­sory and its trad­ing busi­ness into a sin­gle di­vi­sion led by global mar­kets head Brian Chin.</p>
    <p>The re­duc­tions an­nounced on Tues­day are part of an es­ti­mated 400 mil­lion francs in sav­ings ex­pected from the wider re­vamp.</p>
    <p>A sub­stan­tial por­tion of that will be rein­vested into the Swiss busi­ness, es­pe­cially client re­la­tions and digi­ti­sa­tion, the bank said.</p>
    <p>As part of the wider re­or­gan­i­sa­tion in Switzer­land, the com­pany pro­moted Ms Anke Bridge Haux to lead a new dig­i­tal bank­ing busi­ness area in the Swiss Uni­ver­sal Bank, while Mr Daniel Hun­ziker, head of strat­egy at Credit Suisse (Sch­weiz), was tapped to lead the in­sti­tu­tional clients op­er­a­tion.</p>
    <p>Credit Suisse last month said it would ac­cel­er­ate dig­i­tal ef­forts at the Swiss unit and re­duce the costto-in­come ra­tio, a key mea­sure of prof­itabil­ity.</p>
    <p>The job cuts will pri­mar­ily come from sup­port­ing func­tions and the re­duc­tion of bank branches, Mr Helfen­stein said on the call.</p>
    <p>Across Switzer­land, the bank is plan­ning to op­er­ate with 109 lo­ca­tions com­pared with 146 at present by the end of this year. That in­cludes cut­ting branches at 171-yearold Neue Aar­gauer Bank, which has 530 em­ploy­ees and 19 bil­lion francs of as­sets un­der man­age­ment.</p>
    <p>Clients of Neue Aar­gauer Bank will au­to­mat­i­cally be trans­ferred to Credit Suisse fol­low­ing the com­ple­tion of the merger, and they do not need to take any ac­tion at this time, the bank said.</p>

